reviews.text: Free. It was pretty vacant on Thanksgiving week, but this is a gem building and interior. We just wandered around on our own. Beautiful elevators. Interesting WWII cases with ration cards, old recipe books, posters. Building itself has gorgeous old safes (go to basement) and a gallery balcony courtroom that reminds of “To Kill a Mockingbird” scenes. Neat! Worth walking into a long-ago era.

Worth a visit and if you're in Denton go to the Town Square.  Great restaurants, retail stores, coffee shops,  and taverns. Always a diverse group of unique people music and events in the area. The 100 plus year old building is a great backdrop for photos or just to sit and ponder life back then.

Still a working courthouse for the commissioner's court, the county has made great use of its public space with a variety of displays including a small museum. I understand you can rent out the courthouse for weddings or similar events which would be a nice unique space for such an occasion.

Currently under construction. Really looking forward to seeing what it will look like when completed. 
Really wish they had more parking! Especially on the west side of the building.
Good customer service. Don’t have to wait in line for vehicle registrations

I spent a wonderful evening listening to extraordinary musicians from UNT's music school play classical and jazz music. Additionally, some of the students studying opera sang, two sopranos and a baritone. This venue offers musical performances from UNT students and faculty with some regularity, so it's worth keeping an eye on the schedule to see what's happening. The music never disappoints.
A great way to tie town and UNT together.
Great faculty, staff and students. Lots to do an see on campus.
we had a great time celebrating the 3rd anual Denton Black Film Festival. the team at Onthe Square was amazing!
Good artwork shows!
Chicken used is boiled, tender and good flavor. Not bland like most places. Pleasant staff.
The carne asada 🌮 were excellent and filling. Quick service and cold 🍺

Salsa tasted like stewed tomatoes right from the can, chips were stale and the rice has no flavor at all. Chili relleno was good. I wonder if they've changed hands. My past experiences have never been as bad as today's. We probably won't go back.
Fresh Mexican food and quick service. Good vegetarian options. Pinto beans served here without lard. Recommend this place if looking for a quick stop near Lassen Park
Great carnitas tacos and chili rellenos. Good staff

Great place to go when you're in the mood for some Mexican food that's not as expensive as Mi Cocina, and not as cheap as Taco Bell! 

They have good seating inside and out to accommodate different party sizes. One time I even got a cooler from Fuzzy's because they were doing contests and giveaways in the store, and I won!

It was a busy night and I had to wait a bit for my food but the margarita kept me company and the food was hot an fresh when it came out. Music was good and just the right volume to allow for conversation and plenty of screens with multiple sporting events. I will definitely be back.
Good was tasty was always, employees seemed less then happy to here on this fine Thursday evening though. Otherwise it was great, I’ll come back again

Absolutely destroyed my digestive system. As I was up this morning, I can barely stand because of pain in my lower abdomen. My toilet  is an environmental disaster, and will take FEMA weeks to sort out. This is a rarity, as I've ate at this location multiple times over the years, but this is first time it's caused me to physically lose weight  over night.... So I guess employees not properly washing hands, and spending Ecoli, can kinda be a good thing. I guess...

An awesome place to have a cheap outing with friends, or even just have a quick economical lunch. I have visited this Fuzzy's dozens of times over the last 4 years and I can always count on their fast, and friendly staff. The environment is well decorated but not too chaotic. The community is laid back and easy going.

Very pleasantly surprised. I was not expecting much but they managed to convince me on all accounts. The prices are very reasonable and the portions are pretty big. The service was really nice. Out of the things we had I liked the pasta better then pizza but that might be to personal preference. I would definitely come back

It was good food, and served very hot!  The bread is also very yummy.  Nothing really stood out to me, everyone in my group enjoyed their food though.
Bottom line: I would eat here again.
Probably the best old fashioned pizza in town in a total one of a kind, unique atmosphere, very "Italian". Been around for decades. Can't go wrong!

If you're looking for a home cooked Italian style dinner in a comforting setting with the kindest people ever as your server and cook this is the place. We were very impressed with their restaurant and the atmosphere and vibe is perfect!

Come here once a month to celebrate my girlfriend and I's anniversary. Its so cozy, quiet, and you can actually read the menu because the lighting is not too dim. There are only 3 servers but all of them are welcoming and attentive. I always get the chicken florentine, and my girlfriend gets the spaghetti with meatballs and they both taste great! One of the main reasons we keep coming back though is the price! We can get an appetizer, two entrees, and a drink for around 27$ (plus tip) If you're wanting good quality Italian for a bargain, Fera's is the place you should go!

Nice, quiet restaurant with good food. Burgers and street tacos awesome. Lot of beer choices. Do not recommend salmon burgers. Too fishy. Music needs to be light jazz or light classical. Extremely nice staff. Accepts reservations. Prices reasonable.

We have eaten here twice and really enjoyed the experience both times. On our first trip I got a chicken sandwich with avocado and a mango salsa. That was delicious! This time I did a cup of tomato soup, a salad, and a side of fries. For the second time, the food was good and so was the service. I was surprised to see that they also offer brisket tacos from the nearby Juicy Pig BBQ restaurant.

I went in and was seated quickly, and then I gave the waiter my drink. He then quickly forgot about me and I sat silently for 15 minutes before I decided that I should probably go back to class before I’m late. If I wasn’t on a time crunch I probably would have stayed longer or tried to rectify it, but I wasn’t so fortunate. Overall a pretty negative and probably rare experience but it happened. Maybe I’ll try again if I ever feel up to it.
The greenhouse has a magnificent Aura inside. It's very cozy. The bar is mostly where I spend my time as it is very comfortable and has a relaxing setting. The food is to die for.
Ashley did a great job!  Cool place.  Nice ambiance.  Fish n chips was great.

Burgers were fantastic and unique! I had the Stevie, and it was worth it. The prices are very reasonable. The staff was great! The atmosphere was fun and light. Definitely a Five Star worthy establishment!

Great servers and a very nice host... but let me tell y’all about this one couple sitting next to us the “woman” was definitely under 13 and the man well over 40. At first we thought it was a father daughter thing, but then they started holding hands....
I love this place! Tasty food - great music - super atmosphere - awesome service! I can't recommend this place enough. If it is pretty out, you should go up top. It's my favorite!
Great food and fun music. It's a bit too loud and a bit too dark but the food more than makes up for it. The pickled onions are great! I could eat a whole meal just of them.

LSA is one of my favorites. If you stay till around sunset they always pass out beer shots for a sunset toast! How fun!!! I love their burgers of course. The Our Buddy burger is my favorite and their fries will make you feel like you've died and gone to heaven. Anyone from out of town should definitely stop by here for a bite to eat.
One of my favorite places for authentic Mexican food!

Husbands torta was great. My enchiladas tasted a little off but rice and beans were good.  Queso wasn't very good.  Service was awesome and food came out quick. In general a great little place,  will try something different next time.
Great homemade food, friendly service, one of the best Micheladas.
For right now I'm giving 4 out of 5 only because it was my first time and had the carnitas taco combo, Yummy. I'm looking forward to many return visits. Great service as well.
Authentic, fresh, affordable simple Mexican cuisine!
Great BBQ ribs, brisket and sausage. The smoke flavor is perfect. The unique selection of delicious sodas is amazing. They alse have candies you wouldn't find most places.
Outstanding German food. Made fresh. Great selection of craft beer and wine. This place has the largest selection of bottled root beer I've ever seen.
Awesome bbq and prices. Great beer selection.

Everytime I get the friend mushrooms or fried pickles the are not done, the breading appears crispy but is actually doughy inside...this has happened at both locations 4 or 5 times, each time thinking maybe they were rushed, it's the lunch hour, etc...Other than that the burgers are pretty good. Service is good. Just please cook the fried appetizers a couple minutes longer, please! And also the beer batter is not good. Maybe offer without?
Not bad, but not something to write home about either.

I have eaten here for years and every time I visit, I am beyond satisfied. 

1) Excellent price for what you pay. I order a dish for about $10 and I get like a pound of food. I have leftovers twice and it’s never worse than the first time.

2) Consistancy in food quality. I generally order the same thing every time and each time the food meets the standard of the previous time. Some places vary from dine in and take out and every time I have gone, early or late, my foods quality is the same. The ingredients are so tasty and fresh. Take a peek in the kitchen back there and they are working hard!

3) Great service. I am always treated well in store and over the phone. If I have a problem, they meet my needs. If I can say anything negative about them, it’s they sometimes take a while but I prefer quality over quantity any day.

This restaurant is super underrated and I wish more people knew about it! Best Thai in Town!

I came here to Thai Ocha for the first time last month and have gone back almost every week. The Thai Ocha salad and spring rolls are delicious. One con I might add is that I believe they don't give nearly enough peanut dressing for the whole salad and an extra side of the dressing is an additional $2 where they just fill up the original cup of dressing to the top rather than giving another cup of dressing. Besides that, it's a great place!
This place is amazing my family really enjoys coming to eat here. The egg rolls are so good. I will be coming back!

First time here and we loved it. Definitely worth it. We got one of the duck plates and crispy wonton plate with steamed dumplings. It was great and definitely coming back. Our waitress was great and helped us with suggestions.

Fantastic!  I've driven passed this place many times thinking I've got to try that place.  I finally did, and I'm kicking myself for not eating here sooner.  It was REALLY good!  The place itself was very clean and tastefully decorated.  Has about 20 tables, well staffed and knew the food.  Ordered chicken egg rolls for appetizer and plate had 4 large egg rolls sliced in half that were very tasty with sweet & sour sauce.  Ordered the Ocho Thai Seafood at a level 5 (yes, I like spicy).  It had such great flavor.  Mixed seafood was shrimp, crab, scallops, fish, muscle, and at least a couple more, so lots of seafood with the veggies.  The sauce was what made it so special.  Most places are afraid to use spice to flavor the dish like they're going to offend you.  But they don't hold back here.  I can't wait to go back again to get this dish, and try a dessert.  The place was busy, lots of people eating in and some call in orders, but yet it was quiet and you can hear actual conversation.  Most of the tables were full of people, and I must say, not on their phones.  Overall a great dining experience.

Visited the area with clients. High quality dining experience all around. Welcoming and attentive service. Great bartender; enjoyed the Old Fashion. Excellent Tenderloin with peppercorn sauce. Cooked perfectly medium rare with a nice char on exterior. Sides and salads were just average.

Wonderful restaurant!  We live in Dallas and wish we had a place like this closer to us!  Yummy burgers, lobster bisque, quiche for lunch.  Great carrot cake too!  Very lively college atmosphere but quite upscale.  Loved our lunch and can't wait to go back!

Our first night of our trip we ate here, and we wanted to come back every night! The portions are large and our food was delicious. We had the ribs and catfish. The buffalo chips are worth trying too! Everything was tasty and I definitely would suggest this restaurant!

The atmosphere is nice. The staff is attentive and friendly. The drinks are strong. The duck was delicious but, didn't care for the savory pancakes. Personally, I thought they lacked flavor. I would definitely go back and try another dish.
Still one of the best meals I've ever had. Very expensive but absolutely worth the money. Perfect place for a special occasion. Try the prickly pear margarita!

This place is a great steakhouse/ dancehall/ bar to visit! Very rustic, down home kinda feel here. The food was great and the staff was super friendly. Was hungry after loosing a little cash at the casino just north of there, so I figured "let's give it a shot". What a hidden gem this was for great food! Definitely will be back again when I'm up in that part of Texas!

Waitress was awesome and very attentive. The food was good, however I do recommend unless you like a thin cut ribeye, order a steak other than the $6.99 special on Monday and Wednesday. Military discount is honored and the waitress got a 5 star in my book for telling me it was an honor to have been my server.
The steak was very good. Good prices. Friendly attentive waitress. Half price appetizers and margaritas until 7 even on sat.
So glad Trail Dust is now back!!! Went to original for years. Live in McKinney. Make the drive. Can't beat the steaks! Always great! From the service atmosphere to the food always a great experience.

When we first walked In, we were greeted with a pleasant smile and cheerful attitude.  The atmosphere was of country history. The service was very nice. The food was above expectations. The prices are reasonable
 Free beans, and bread. A dance floor, stage for live music on Saturday's.  Juke box
And a cool slide. Bar. Clean restrooms. Good place for adults to get out, with, or without your kids. Easy access off and back on the highway.  Lunch specials till 3:00 pm. Plenty of truck parking as well.
